			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There is no other word in the dictionary that more accurately portrays the English summer than &#8216;fickle&#8217;. What can be a glorious day one moment can quickly (and often does) deteriorate into the drizzly normality we have come to expect. So you&#8217;ll forgive me, then, for thinking ahead to the winter snow season in mid-July.</p>
<p>Currently, I have two trips cemented in place, with a third in the early planning stages. First-up I have my annual family trip away with my Dad and Brother. In January 2012 we&#8217;ll be heading to Val Thorens, France. I&#8217;ve heard the powder is fantastic, so I&#8217;m itching to get back on my board and into the white stuff.</p>
<p>In March I&#8217;m heading back to Zermatt, Switzerland. It&#8217;s such a wonderful resort that I&#8217;m already excited at the prospect.</p>
<p>Finally, I&#8217;m looking to sort a trip in February with my Uni mates. I&#8217;m not sure on the destination yet, but it&#8217;ll be somewhere snow-sure with a good party vibe. Ischgl is a strong possibility.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/fUTfgNiMWla4XrhB8uRwVN4m-UE/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/fUTfgNiMWla4XrhB8uRwVN4m-UE/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
