		<description><![CDATA[<p>Big White will always have a special place in my heart. It&#8217;s the first ski resort I ever went to and, as a result, is the place I learned to ski. I&#8217;m pretty lucky in the sense that I learned in absolutely perfect conditions. Not only was the snow the best I&#8217;ve ever skied on, [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Big White will always have a special place in my heart. It&#8217;s the first ski resort I ever went to and, as a result, is the place I learned to ski. I&#8217;m pretty lucky in the sense that I learned in absolutely perfect conditions. Not only was the snow the best I&#8217;ve ever skied on, but I was the only person in my lesson group &#8211; essentially bagging me a heavily-discounted private lesson.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_713" class="wp-caption aligncenter" style="width: 522px"><a href="http://howardlloyd.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/IMG_0601.jpg" rel="lightbox[712]"><img class="size-medium wp-image-713  " title="IMG_0601" src="http://howardlloyd.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/IMG_0601.jpg" alt="" width="512" height="384" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Powder heaven. Big White, Feb. 2009</p></div>
<p>The good:</p>
<ul>
<li>The snow is unbelievable. Big White&#8217;s tagline is, &#8216;It&#8217;s the snow&#8221;, and it&#8217;s easy to see why. There&#8217;s so much snow that the evergreen trees have been nicknamed <a href="http://www.erikhenne.com/images/Big%20White%20snow%20ghosts%20with%20sun%20tree%20covered%20in%20snow%202.jpg" target="_blank" rel="lightbox[712]">snow ghosts</a>.</li>
<li>The village has a real ski resort charm to it.</li>
<li>The scenery is fantastic.</li>
<li>The ski school is excellent and is highly recommended.</li>
<li>Lift system is speedy and copes with the crowds.</li>
</ul>
<p>The bad:</p>
<ul>
<li>The resort is pretty small, both the village itself and the extent of the pistes.</li>
<li>It&#8217;s a bit of a treck to get to. The nearest airport is Kelowna, and it&#8217;s about a 2hr drive from the airport to the resort. If you&#8217;re flying in from anywhere other than BC you&#8217;ll typically have to fly via Vancouver.</li>
</ul>
<p>Rating: 8/10. If you&#8217;re looking for a family-friendly, more intimate resort than Whistler/Blackcomb, you&#8217;d can do a lot worse than Big White. While there are some drawbacks, the snow quality more than makes up for it. I still have dreams about all that wonderful, wonderful powder&#8230;</p>

<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/OvzPmlIa_3cJbGDRPJbzBoLYbsk/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/OvzPmlIa_3cJbGDRPJbzBoLYbsk/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
<a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/OvzPmlIa_3cJbGDRPJbzBoLYbsk/1/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/OvzPmlIa_3cJbGDRPJbzBoLYbsk/1/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/HowardsTravelBlog/~4/lCR8h-uAWI0" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
