		<description><![CDATA[<p>Val d&#8217;Isere is undoubtedly one of my favourite European resorts. The combination of extensive pistes, guaranteed snow and village charm make an attractive package. With access to neighbouring Tignes, it&#8217;s possible to ski all day, every day and have little repition. The off piste action is also superb, with many spots serviced by drag lifts [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Val d&#8217;Isere is undoubtedly one of my favourite European resorts. The combination of extensive pistes, guaranteed snow and village charm make an attractive package. With access to neighbouring Tignes, it&#8217;s possible to ski all day, every day and have little repition. The off piste action is also superb, with many spots serviced by drag lifts or similar.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="wp-caption aligncenter" style="width: 372px"><a href="http://a2.sphotos.ak.fbcdn.net/hphotos-ak-ash1/29328_582173070350_200900291_34753187_6730753_n.jpg" rel="lightbox[694]"><img class=" " title="val" src="http://a2.sphotos.ak.fbcdn.net/hphotos-ak-ash1/29328_582173070350_200900291_34753187_6730753_n.jpg" alt="" width="362" height="483" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Val d&#39;Isere village, March 2010</p></div>
<p>The good:</p>
<ul>
<li>Snow snow snow. Even during years where the average snowfall across the Alps is less than stellar, Val d&#8217;Isere receives enough of the white stuff to allow for off piste powder forays.</li>
<li>Quality of restaurants is superb.</li>
<li>Location is great, with easy access to Tignes and other resorts such as Les Arcs a short trip away.</li>
</ul>
<p>The bad:</p>
<ul>
<li>Price. It is the main factor that prevents most people from staying in Val d&#8217;Isere itself. Lots opt to stay in the relatively cheaper (but uglier and quieter) Tignes.</li>
<li>Not the easiest resort to get to, with around a 2hr+ drive from Chambery airport and long, winding road with little overtaking opportunities.</li>
</ul>
<p>Rating: 10/10. There&#8217;s not many resorts that can compete with Val d&#8217;Isere for snow and piste extent (Zermatt being the main contender), and it&#8217;s a place that every keen skier or boarder should experience at least once in their life. It&#8217;s a wonderful resort.</p>

<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/Axe5WT05Goz_Fw4hC5cq2AVX0ss/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/Axe5WT05Goz_Fw4hC5cq2AVX0ss/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
