		<description><![CDATA[<p>Obergurgl (and its neighbour, Hochgurgl) represent what Austria has to offer: reliable snow, charming villages and crazy aprés-ski. Obergurgl was the second resort in Europe I skied, and while I am unlikely to go back any time soon, I definitely recommend it, particularly for beginners.</p> <p>The good:</p> It&#8217;s a high resort, so the snow is [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Obergurgl (and its neighbour, Hochgurgl) represent what Austria has to offer: reliable snow, charming villages and crazy aprés-ski. Obergurgl was the second resort in Europe I skied, and while I am unlikely to go back any time soon, I definitely recommend it, particularly for beginners.</p>
<div class="wp-caption aligncenter" style="width: 372px"><a href="http://howardlloyd.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/obergurgl.jpg" rel="lightbox[675]"><img class=" " title="obergurgl" src="http://howardlloyd.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/obergurgl.jpg" alt="" width="362" height="483" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Taken from the top of Hochgurgl, Jan. 2010</p></div>
<p>The good:</p>
<ul>
<li>It&#8217;s a high resort, so the snow is reliable. The Ötztal valley is known for its snow, and Obergurgl/Hochgurgl gets the best of it.</li>
<li>Aprés-ski is one of its strong points. The Nederhütte is famous (ranked 3rd best Aprés bar in Austria), and while the village is pretty quiet, there are some good spots (Josl Kellar being one)</li>
<li>Relatively quiet, so the pistes don&#8217;t get busy.</li>
<li>Great for beginners!</li>
</ul>
<p>The bad:</p>
<ul>
<li>You will eventually end up doing the same runs day after day. Piste variety is not one of the strong points.</li>
<li>Relatively quiet village, despite the few places that are rocking.</li>
<li>Not so great for experts, though there is some wonderful off-piste action to be had.</li>
</ul>
<p>Rating: 7/10. The snow quality is what bumps up the score, as does the aprés, but aside from that I have no real desire to head back to Obergurgl any time soon.</p>

<p><a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/INNsJPPtJS0Tt_OCdtSiuAP3ufI/0/da"><img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/INNsJPPtJS0Tt_OCdtSiuAP3ufI/0/di" border="0" ismap="true"></img></a><br/>
